        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-09-22T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-09-22T16:00:00-05:00" n="257"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                <head>257. Memorandum of a Conversation Between the President and the Secretary of
                    State, White House, Washington, September 22, 1956, 5 p.m.<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d257fn1">Source: Eisenhower Library, Dulles Papers,
                        Meetings With the President. Secret; Personal and Private. Drafted by
                            <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date"
                            when="1956-09-22T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 22, 1956, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I called on the President at about 5:00 in the afternoon. We talked for about a
                    half hour with reference to the Suez Canal matter. I reported to him the recent
                    developments, thus supplementing my personal cables to him. The President
                    expressed satisfaction at the outcome.</p>
                <p>I referred to the private talk which I had had with <persName corresp="#p_ERHSA1"
                        >Anthony Eden</persName> and to the possible military measures which he had
                        outlined.<note n="2" xml:id="d257fn2">See <ref target="#d245">Document
                            245</ref>.</note> The President expressed some skepticism as to whether
                    they would be decisive.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">JFD</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <note n="3" xml:id="d257fn3">
                            <persName corresp="#p_MWB1">Macomber</persName> initialed for <persName
                                corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
